Note:
FFI Constants - Foreign Function Interface Constant Definitions (P2-D, D-FFI-06)

This file is the single source of truth for FFI-related compile-time constants.
The compiler frontend (parser/ast/hir), the IR pipeline (mir/lir), the codegen
backends (per-arch asm_generator + calling_convention), the driver
(compile_orchestrator + linker_driver), and the runtime resolver
(ffi_loader/ffi_resolver/ffi_caller/ffi_marshaler) all consume these constants
to keep the calling-convention identifiers, link-type identifiers, ABI type
identifiers, and platform identifiers consistent across the entire toolchain.

Per CEO Q5 ratification, FFI constants live under runtime/integration/ffi/
because they are inherently shared between the compiler and the runtime
resolver. The compiler-side parser/ast/hir/mir/lir continue to inline a
small subset of these constants for legacy compatibility — the canonical
definitions are here.
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Calling Convention IDs
Note: ============================================================================
Note: These IDs are stored in AST_EXTERNAL_DECLARATION (offset 128), in
Note: HIRExternalDeclaration (offset 152), in MIRFunction (offset 112), and in
Note: LIRFunction (offset 160). The codegen backend reads the convention_id
Note: and dispatches argument register assignment + stack discipline through
Note: the appropriate per-arch calling-convention module.

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_C as Integer is 0
Note:    System V on Unix-likes (Linux/Darwin/FreeBSD/NetBSD/OpenBSD), Win64 on Windows.
Note:    Default convention. SysV on x86_64: rdi/rsi/rdx/rcx/r8/r9 for ints,
Note:    xmm0-xmm7 for floats, return in rax/xmm0. Caller cleans up stack.

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_STDCALL as Integer is 1
Note:    Windows i386 legacy. All args on stack right-to-left, callee cleans.
Note:    On x86_64-Windows, stdcall degenerates to Win64 (per MSDN).

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_FASTCALL as Integer is 2
Note:    Windows i386 fastcall. First 2 int args in ECX, EDX; rest on stack;
Note:    callee cleans. On x86_64-Windows, degenerates to Win64.

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_CDECL as Integer is 3
Note:    Synonym for `c` on Unix-likes (System V). On Windows i386 it differs
Note:    from stdcall: cdecl is caller-cleanup. On x86_64, behaves like SysV.

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_SYSCALL as Integer is 4
Note:    Direct OS syscall — kernel entry. Linux x86_64: rax=syscall_no,
Note:    rdi/rsi/rdx/r10/r8/r9 = args, syscall instruction. Return in rax,
Note:    errno via negative return.

Constant FFI_CALLING_CONV_OBJC as Integer is 5
Note:    Objective-C method-call ABI (Q3 CEO amendment 2026-05-24).
Note:    Lowered as objc_msgSend dispatch: first arg = receiver (id),
Note:    second arg = selector (SEL — resolved from __objc_selrefs),
Note:    remaining args follow SysV C ABI. Darwin-only; non-Darwin
Note:    targets reject objc-convention externals at link time.

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Link Type IDs
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Per Q1 CEO ratification: default link_type is `dynamic`.

Constant FFI_LINK_TYPE_DEFAULT as Integer is 0
Note:    Default = dynamic. Resolved via runtime dlopen/dlsym or PLT/GOT.

Constant FFI_LINK_TYPE_STATIC as Integer is 1
Note:    Static linking — linker emits -l<lib> and resolves at link time.

Constant FFI_LINK_TYPE_DYNAMIC as Integer is 2
Note:    Dynamic linking — runtime resolver loads library at first call.

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FFI Flag Bits (stored in flags field of AST/HIR/MIR external nodes)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant FFI_FLAG_UNSAFE as Integer is 1
Note:    Bit 0: external is marked `unsafe`. Per Q4 CEO amendment 2026-05-24,
Note:    calls to unsafe externals OUTSIDE an Unsafe Block are compile-time errors.

Constant FFI_FLAG_LAZY_LOAD as Integer is 2
Note:    Bit 1: symbol resolution deferred until first call (vs. process-start
Note:    pre-resolve). Reduces startup cost when many externals are declared.

Constant FFI_FLAG_VARIADIC as Integer is 4
Note:    Bit 2: external has variadic parameters (`... as Variadic` in source).
Note:    SysV ABI requires AL register = float-arg-count at call sites.

Constant FFI_FLAG_LINK_TYPE_EXPLICIT as Integer is 8
Note:    Bit 3: source explicitly specified link_type; otherwise default applies.

Constant FFI_FLAG_CONVENTION_EXPLICIT as Integer is 16
Note:    Bit 4: source explicitly specified convention; otherwise default applies.

Constant FFI_FLAG_EXCEPTION_SAFE as Integer is 32
Note:    Bit 5: external supports exception propagation across FFI boundary.
Note:    Wires through to longjmp-style fault handler integration.

Note: ============================================================================
Note: C ABI Type IDs (used by type_marshal.runa and per-arch register dispatch)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: When a Runa type crosses an FFI boundary, marshal_runa_type_to_c_type
Note: maps the HIR type to one of these C ABI categories. The categories drive
Note: the per-arch register-assignment decision (integer reg vs. float reg vs.
Note: stack vs. compound).

Constant C_TYPE_VOID as Integer is 0
Constant C_TYPE_BOOL as Integer is 1
Constant C_TYPE_INT8 as Integer is 2
Constant C_TYPE_UINT8 as Integer is 3
Constant C_TYPE_INT16 as Integer is 4
Constant C_TYPE_UINT16 as Integer is 5
Constant C_TYPE_INT32 as Integer is 6
Constant C_TYPE_UINT32 as Integer is 7
Constant C_TYPE_INT64 as Integer is 8
Note:    Default mapping for Runa Integer (per spec §3604-3618 — fixed-width 64-bit).
Constant C_TYPE_UINT64 as Integer is 9
Constant C_TYPE_FLOAT as Integer is 10
Constant C_TYPE_DOUBLE as Integer is 11
Note:    Default mapping for Runa Float.
Constant C_TYPE_CHAR as Integer is 12
Note:    Single-byte char (signed).
Constant C_TYPE_PCHAR as Integer is 13
Note:    Pointer-to-char — used for C string parameters (const char* by default).
Constant C_TYPE_PVOID as Integer is 14
Note:    Generic pointer (void*).
Constant C_TYPE_STRUCT_SMALL as Integer is 15
Note:    Struct ≤16 bytes — SysV passes in two GPRs (RAX:RDX) or XMM regs.
Constant C_TYPE_STRUCT_LARGE as Integer is 16
Note:    Struct >16 bytes — passed by hidden-pointer / sret semantics.

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Platform IDs (used by linker_driver and runtime resolver)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant FFI_PLATFORM_LINUX as Integer is 1
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_DARWIN as Integer is 2
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_WINDOWS as Integer is 3
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_FREEBSD as Integer is 4
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_OPENBSD as Integer is 5
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_NETBSD as Integer is 6
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_WASI as Integer is 7
Constant FFI_PLATFORM_BARE_METAL as Integer is 8

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Library Name Encoding (used by runtime resolver)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Source declarations like `from library "c"` are translated by the linker
Note: driver to platform-specific library names:
Note:   Linux/BSD:  "c" -> "libc.so.6"   (dlopen)
Note:   Darwin:     "c" -> "libc.dylib"  (dlopen)
Note:   Windows:    "c" -> "msvcrt.dll"  (LoadLibrary)
Note: The runtime resolver consults these mappings for dynamic loading.

Constant FFI_DLOPEN_FLAG_LAZY as Integer is 1
Note:    RTLD_LAZY — resolve symbols on first reference (default).

Constant FFI_DLOPEN_FLAG_NOW as Integer is 2
Note:    RTLD_NOW — resolve all symbols immediately at dlopen time.

Constant FFI_DLOPEN_FLAG_GLOBAL as Integer is 256
Note:    RTLD_GLOBAL — symbols visible to subsequently-loaded libraries.

Constant FFI_DLOPEN_FLAG_LOCAL as Integer is 0
Note:    RTLD_LOCAL — symbols private to this library (default).

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Resolver State Codes
Note: ============================================================================
Note: The runtime resolver uses these codes when populating per-symbol thunk
Note: slots and reporting resolution errors.

Constant FFI_RESOLVE_OK as Integer is 0
Constant FFI_RESOLVE_LIBRARY_NOT_FOUND as Integer is 1
Constant FFI_RESOLVE_SYMBOL_NOT_FOUND as Integer is 2
Constant FFI_RESOLVE_OUT_OF_MEMORY as Integer is 3
Constant FFI_RESOLVE_INVALID_HANDLE as Integer is 4
Constant FFI_RESOLVE_PLATFORM_UNSUPPORTED as Integer is 5

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ABI Register-Set Categories (per-arch dispatch helpers consume these)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant FFI_REG_CLASS_INTEGER as Integer is 0
Note:    Integer/pointer/bool category — argument passes in an integer GPR.

Constant FFI_REG_CLASS_FLOAT as Integer is 1
Note:    Float/double category — argument passes in a vector register.

Constant FFI_REG_CLASS_MEMORY as Integer is 2
Note:    Argument passes on the stack (after all reg slots are exhausted or
Note:    when type is too large for registers).

Constant FFI_REG_CLASS_AGGREGATE as Integer is 3
Note:    Struct/union category — the per-arch ABI dispatcher classifies each
Note:    eightbyte of the aggregate using the platform's algorithm (SysV ABI
Note:    §3.2.3 for x86_64; AAPCS64 §6.4 for AArch64) and produces an ordered
Note:    sequence of FFI_REG_CLASS_INTEGER / FFI_REG_CLASS_FLOAT /
Note:    FFI_REG_CLASS_MEMORY slots that the caller uses to marshal the
Note:    aggregate. The classifier is invoked at MIR->LIR lowering time when
Note:    a call site passes an aggregate argument; see lir_builder.lower_call.
